<item>
            <title>[DERBY-538] Investigate using the standard java.net.URLClassLoader for database class loading.</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-538</link>
                <project id="10594" key="DERBY">Derby</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Would change the fix for &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/DERBY-537&quot; title=&quot;SQLJ.INSTALL_JAR and SQLJ.UPDATE_JAR fail when running with a SecurityManager enabled.&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;DERBY-537&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;DERBY-537&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;) so that&apos;s why it is a sub-task.&lt;br/&gt;
Use of the standard class loader would reduce security concerns and allow jars stored in the database to take advantage of standard features such as package sealing.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
